                <p>The researchers conclude (<em>step 4</em>) that since the p-value is so
                    small<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101129T182153-0500"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
                    the data provide extremely strong evidence to reject
                        <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101129T182205-0500"?>H<sub>o</sub><?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101129T182203-0500" content="Ho"?>
                    and conclude that age and legibility distance are linearly related.</p>
                <!--<activity idref="_u5_m2_dig11" purpose="didigetthis"/>-->
                <wb:inline idref="u4_m4_qq2_tutor3" purpose="didigetthis"/>
                <activity idref="_u5_m2_lbd12" purpose="learnbydoing"/>
                <p>
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101129T204536-0500" comment="I think ti is confusing the way these three examples are all mixed up -- trying to keep track of what&apos;s going on in three exmaples at once might hinder students&apos; understanding. Consider streamlining this section. "?><em>Note:</em>
                    It is important<?oxy_comment_end?> to distinguish between the information
                    provided by r and by the p-value. The correlation coefficient <em>r informs us
                        about the strength of the linear relationship in the data</em>: close to +1
                    or -1 for a strong linear relationship, close to 0 for a weak linear
                    relationship. In contrast, the regression <em>p-value informs us about the
                        strength of evidence</em> that there is a linear relationship in the
                    population from which the data were obtained.</p>
                <p>In our example, since the p-value is 0.000 and r = -.801, we would say that we
                    have extremely strong evidence of a fairly strong relationship between age and
                    distance in the population of drivers.</p>
